claim.claim-text:
1. A suturing apparatus, comprising:
a tubular housing having a longitudinal axis, a lumen and a distal end;
a first jaw and a second jaw located at the distal end of the tubular housing, one of the jaws moveable relative to the other;
a puncturing projection substantially positioned and completely slideable within the lumen of the tubular housing and with a sharpened tip pointing along its longitudinal axis in a substantially straight first stressed position, having a distal portion and carrying a suture, the puncturing projection movable, while the jaws are closed around tissue, between the first position wherein the distal portion of the puncturing projection is substantially contained within an area between the first jaw and the second jaw and a substantially curved second resting position wherein the distal portion of the puncturing projection extends through and beyond an opening in the first jaw along a path which is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the tubular housing; wherein the opening in the first jaw is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the tubular housing,
wherein the puncturing projection comprises a wire having a diameter of about 0.04 inches and a slot having a length of about 0.12 inches disposed in the distal portion for carrying the suture, and
wherein in the substantially curved second resting position, the puncturing projection has a radius of curvature that is at least three times the diameter of the wire.

13. A method for suturing a piece of tissue, comprising the steps of:
engaging a suture with a naturally curved puncturing projection with a sharpened tip pointing along its longitudinal axis of a suturing apparatus having a first jaw and a second jaw, the naturally curved puncturing projection comprising a wire having a diameter of about 0.04 inches, the suture being engaged by an opening in a wall of the puncturing projection, the opening having a length of about 0.12 inches, the naturally curved puncturing projection having a radius of curvature that is at least three times the diameter of the wire;
capturing the piece of tissue between the first jaw and the second jaw;
carrying the suture through the piece of tissue with the puncturing projection as the puncturing projection slides within a lumen of the suturing apparatus while the jaws are closed around tissue;
extending the suture through a transverse opening in the first jaw along a path which is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the suturing apparatus;
releasing the suture from the puncturing projection; and
retracting the puncturing projection from the tissue.

20. A suturing device, comprising:
a tubular housing having a lumen and a distal end;
a first jaw and a second jaw having longitudinal axes and connected at the distal end of the tubular housing, one of the jaws moveable relative to the other;
a puncturing projection substantially positioned and completely slideable within the lumen of the tubular housing and having a sharpened tip pointing along its longitudinal axis in a substantially straight first stressed position, the puncturing projection comprising a wire having a diameter of about 0.04 inches and a slot having a length of about 0.12 inches to engage a suture strand;
wherein either one of the first or second jaws includes an accommodating gap, which is substantially perpendicular to its longitudinal axis, for the puncturing projection having a distal portion that is movable, while the jaws are closed around tissue, between the first position wherein the distal portion is substantially contained within an area between the first jaw and the second jaw and a substantially curved second resting position wherein the distal portion of the puncturing projection extends through and beyond the jaw along a path which is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the jaw, and
wherein in the substantially curved second resting position, the puncturing projection has a radius of curvature that is at least three times the diameter of the wire.

25. A suturing device, comprising:
a tubular housing having a longitudinal axis, a lumen and a distal end;
two jaws located at the distal end of the tubular housing and moveable relative to each other about a pivot point;
a puncturing projection substantially positioned and completely slideable within the lumen of the tubular housing and having a sharpened tip pointing along its longitudinal axis in a substantially straight first stressed position, the puncturing projection comprising a wire having a diameter of about 0.04 inches and a slot having a length of about 0.12 inches to engage a suture strand;
wherein one jaw includes a distal portion having an accommodating gap for the puncturing projection that is movable, while the jaws are closed around tissue, between the first position wherein the puncturing projection is substantially contained within an area between the two jaws and a substantially curved second resting position wherein the puncturing projection extends through the accommodating gap and beyond the jaws along a path which is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the tubular housing; wherein the accommodating gap in the jaw is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the tubular housing, and
wherein in the substantially curved second resting position, the puncturing projection has a radius of curvature that is at least three times the diameter of the wire.

30. A suturing device, comprising:
a tubular base having a longitudinal axis, a lumen and a distal end;
a pair of jaws positioned at the distal end of the tubular base and one jaw moveable relative to the base about a pivot point;
a puncturing projection substantially positioned and completely slideable within the lumen of the tubular base and having a sharpened tip pointing along its longitudinal axis in a substantially straight first stressed position, the puncturing projection comprising a wire having a diameter of about 0.04 inches and a slot having a length of about 0.12 inches to engage a suture strand;
wherein the one moveable jaw includes a distal portion having an accommodating gap, which is substantially transverse to a longitudinal axis of the jaw, for the projection that is movable, while the jaws are closed around tissue, between the first position wherein the projection is substantially contained within an area between the jaw and the base and a substantially curved second resting position wherein the projection extends through the accommodating gap and beyond the tubular base along a path which is substantially perpendicular to the longitudinal axis of the tubular base, and
wherein in the substantially curved second resting position, the puncturing projection has a radius of curvature that is at least three times the diameter of the wire.
